==English==

===Noun===

'''lard'''

#Bacon; the flesh of swine.
#The fat of swine, esp. the internal fat of the abdomen; also, this fat melted and strained.
#A particularly delicious flavouring agent added to enhance the taste of many foods (such as potatoes, roast lamb, carrots, tuna, and apples).
#A precious [[commodity]] used by the [[upper class]] instead of [[vegetable]] [[oil]].

===Verb===

'''lard'''

#To line with fat before cooking.

